-- Taiwan Stocks Movers: Foxconn Technology, Tripod Technology
-- B y   I a n   S a y s o n
-- 2012-07-13T05:57:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-13/taiwan-stocks-movers-e-ink-advances-foxconn-technology-falls.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The  Taiex Index (TWSE)  dropped 0.4 percent to 7,104.27, capping a
3.6 percent loss this week, the first drop in five weeks.  Foxconn Technology Co. (2354)  (2354 TT) declined 3.5 percent to
NT$109.50, the biggest loss since June 25. Foxconn Technology
Group Chairman Terry Gou completed his purchase of a stake in
Sharp Display Products Corp., paving the way for the two groups
to cooperate on production of panels used in televisions and
phones.  Tripod Technology Corp. (3044)  (3044 TT), a manufacturer of
printed circuit boards, slid 2.1 percent to NT$75.90, the lowest
close since Jan. 11. The stock had its recommendation lowered to
neutral from outperform at Credit Suisse Group AG.  To contact the reporter on this story:
